cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on real-time queries of surveillance video data using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes a collaborative cloud-edge system for load balancing and achieving the latency-accuracy tradeoff. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses a CNN training scheme to reduce training time with high accuracy. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for video analysis and decision-making. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with large-scale surveillance video streams and real-time queries.
